<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">71.1.21/507 Supp’l: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-30T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            30, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Kindly advise effect produced by Department’s October 13, 10 p.m. and
                                October 14, 8 p.m. and indicate what action you think Colombia is
                                likely to take with respect to new proposed subsoil agreement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>